name: PedroSalce COSC 1336 final project
short_description:
Once the program is open you are provided with two sets of data, Project-Data-1.txt and Project-Data-2.txt. 
This set of data has information of Healthy and Diseased people and the amount of different bacteria present in their systems.
The program also calculates the average bacteria present in their bodies.
Once the averages are given, the program compares the averages to determine what bacteria occur significantly less and which occur more in diseased than healthy.
Now the program automatically opens the second set of data, Project-Data-2.txt. This set of data contains samples from other people.
Using the information provided from the data from the first set of data, Project-Data-1.txt, the program compares the second set to determine whether the subjects are healthy or diseased.
